{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"alias":"baby-adorable-goose","description":"On every autodeploy restart the review-bot silently abandons acknowledged-but-unreviewed\nwebhooks (the in-memory review queue is dropped), so changes stall until the slow backfill\nreconciler catches up — and the reconciler itself can be frozen indefinitely by one hung\nreview. Drain the queue on graceful shutdown and give backfill reviews the same per-review\ntimeout the live worker has.\n\n## Why\nThe review queue is an in-memory `asyncio.Queue` (`app.py:107`). `POST /webhook` enqueues and\nreturns `202 {\"queued\": true}` — a promise to process the event. But the lifespan shutdown\n(`app.py:127-134`) **cancels the worker without draining the queue**, so on the hourly\nautodeploy restart (ADR-0026) any enqueued-but-unreviewed event is lost, and any in-flight\nreview is cancelled. Recovery falls entirely to the reconcile backfill, which is slow (300s\ninterval; sequential full-LLM-review per change; cursor advanced only at end-of-pass,\n`reconcile.py:221`). This was observed live: an autodeploy at ~22:53Z dropped a batch of\nin-flight webhooks (changes 716-723) that then took ~25 min to drain. Separately, the worker\nwraps each review in `asyncio.wait_for(..., timeout)` (`app.py:153`) but `reconcile_once` calls\n`review_and_vote` with NO timeout (`reconcile.py:215`) — so a single hung backfill review would\nfreeze ALL backfill indefinitely (the safety-net has no safety-net).\n\n## What\n1. **Graceful drain (app.py lifespan):** in the shutdown `finally`, BEFORE cancelling the\n   worker, `await asyncio.wait_for(queue.join(), timeout=SHUTDOWN_DRAIN_SECONDS)` (suppressing\n   TimeoutError) so queued events are processed by the still-running worker before exit;\n   anything not drained in the window still falls to the reconciler (fail-safe, not fail-lose).\n   `SHUTDOWN_DRAIN_SECONDS` from env (default 45).\n2. **stop_grace_period (docker-compose.yml):** set the review-bot service `stop_grace_period`\n   to 60s so Docker's SIGTERM→SIGKILL window is long enough for the drain to run (default 10s\n   would SIGKILL mid-drain).\n3. **Reconciler timeout parity (reconcile.py):** wrap the `review_and_vote` call in\n   `reconcile_once` in `asyncio.wait_for(..., timeout=<review_timeout>)`; on TimeoutError emit a\n   greppable marker and CONTINUE to the next candidate (never freeze the loop). Share the\n   timeout value with the worker (factor `review_timeout_seconds()` so both read the same\n   `REVIEW_TIMEOUT_SECONDS`).\n\n## Scope\n- `src/rebar/review_bot/app.py`: drain in lifespan `finally`; `SHUTDOWN_DRAIN_SECONDS` helper.\n- `src/rebar/review_bot/reconcile.py`: per-review `wait_for` + timeout marker + continue.\n- `src/rebar/review_bot/config.py` (or a small shared helper): `review_timeout_seconds()` used\n  by both app and reconcile (DRY; avoids an app<->reconcile import cycle).\n- `infra/compose/docker-compose.yml`: `stop_grace_period: 60s` on `review-bot`.\n- `tests/unit/test_review_bot.py`: RED tests for the drain and the reconciler timeout.\n- Non-goal: replacing the in-memory queue with a persistent/disk-backed queue (heavier; the\n  reconciler remains the ultimate recovery path — chosen approach per operator direction).\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] On lifespan shutdown with items still queued, the items are drained (processed by the\n      worker) rather than dropped; before the fix they are dropped.\n      Proving command: `python -m pytest tests/unit/test_review_bot.py -k shutdown_drain -q`\n      passes and is confirmed RED on the pre-fix tree.\n- [ ] The drain is bounded: if draining exceeds `SHUTDOWN_DRAIN_SECONDS`, shutdown still\n      completes (does not hang) and remaining items are left for the reconciler.\n      Proving command: a test with a slow/blocking worker asserts shutdown returns within the\n      bound.\n- [ ] `reconcile_once` does not hang on a review that never returns: a review exceeding the\n      timeout is abandoned, a marker is emitted, and the loop proceeds to the next candidate.\n      Proving command: `python -m pytest tests/unit/test_review_bot.py -k reconcile_timeout -q`\n      passes and is confirmed RED on the pre-fix tree.\n- [ ] `infra/compose/docker-compose.yml` sets `stop_grace_period` on the review-bot service.\n      Proving command: `python -c \"import yaml; d=yaml.safe_load(open('infra/compose/docker-compose.yml')); assert d['services']['review-bot'].get('stop_grace_period')\"`\n- [ ] Existing gates stay green.\n      Proving command: `make lint && make typecheck && python -m pytest tests/unit/test_review_bot.py -q` all exit 0.","id":"89be-888d-b127-449a","parent_id":"","priority":2,"tags":[],"ticket_type":"task","title":"review-bot: drain review queue on shutdown + reconciler per-review timeout (deploy resilience)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"CREATE","timestamp":1784158138487073001,"uuid":"7bea0832-13d2-44e6-972e-36f34bba5a44"}